  "notes": [
    {
      "id": "fa756f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralTitle",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 0,
      "content": "ADMISSIONS INFORMATION FOR ALL MAJORS",
      "contentHtml": null
    },
    {
      "id": "a2936f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralText",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 1,
      "content": "All transfer applicants must meet the University of California admissions eligibility requirements and the campus’s admission selection criteria. All requirements must be completed by the end of the spring term prior to transfer. For more information on UC admissions eligibility and admission to UC Santa Cruz, visit the Admissions website . The UC Santa Cruz Transfer Admission Guarantee (TAG) is a formal agreement that guarantees your fall admission to your chosen major, provided you are transferring from a California Community College and meet specific requirements. Visit the UC Santa Cruz TAG webpage for more information.",
      "contentHtml": "<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">All transfer applicants must meet the University of California admissions eligibility requirements and the campus’s admission selection criteria. All requirements must be completed by the end of the spring term prior to transfer. For more information on UC admissions eligibility and admission to UC Santa Cruz, visit the </span><a href=\"https://admissions.ucsc.edu/attend-ucsc/transfer-students\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Admissions website</a><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">.</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"font-size: 14px;\">The UC Santa Cruz Transfer Admission Guarantee (TAG)</strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"> is a formal agreement that guarantees your fall admission to your chosen major, provided you are transferring from a California Community College and meet specific requirements. Visit the </span><a href=\"https://admissions.ucsc.edu/transfer-admission-guarantee-tag\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-size: 14px;\">UC Santa Cruz TAG webpage</a><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"> for more information.</span></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "edd56237-c5a3-444d-b8b4-0193dca5d02f",
      "type": "GeneralTitle",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 2,
      "content": "IMPORTANT MAJOR PREPARATION",
      "contentHtml": null
    },
    {
      "id": "399a6f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralText",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 3,
      "content": "This is a non-screening major: completion of specific major coursework is not required for admission. However, students are strongly encouraged to complete as many lower-division courses as possible from the \" Recommended Preparation \" section below to support timely degree completion. Students applying to non-screening majors are also encouraged to complete the California General Education Transfer Curriculum (Cal-GETC) or all UC Santa Cruz general education requirements prior to transfer. For guidance on incorporating Cal-GETC into your academic plan, consult your community college counselor.",
      "contentHtml": "<p><strong style=\"font-size: 14px;\">This is a non-screening major: </strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">completion of specific major coursework is not required for admission. However, students are strongly encouraged to complete as many lower-division courses as possible from the \"</span><strong style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Recommended Preparation</strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">\" section below to support timely degree completion.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Students applying to </span><a href=\"https://admissions.ucsc.edu/posts/non-screening-majors\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-size: 14px;\">non-screening majors</a><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"> are also encouraged to complete the </span><a href=\"https://admission.universityofcalifornia.edu/admission-requirements/transfer-requirements/preparing-to-transfer/general-education-igetc/cal-getc/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>California General Education Transfer Curriculum (Cal-GETC)</strong></a><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"> or all UC Santa Cruz general education requirements prior to transfer. For guidance on incorporating Cal-GETC into your academic plan, consult your community college counselor.</span></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "358aa63a-21af-4d51-9845-0193dca5d030",
      "type": "GeneralTitle",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 4,
      "content": "EXAM CREDIT",
      "contentHtml": null
    },
    {
      "id": "d7996f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralText",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 5,
      "content": "Some Advanced Placement (AP), International Baccalaureate Higher Level (IBH), and Advanced Level (A-level) exams satisfy UCSC course requirements. UCSC's exam credit policies may be found on the Degree Progress Unit website .",
      "contentHtml": "<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Some Advanced Placement (AP), International Baccalaureate Higher Level&nbsp;(IBH), and Advanced Level (A-level) exams satisfy UCSC course requirements. UCSC's exam credit policies may be found on the </span><a href=\"https://degreeprogress.ucsc.edu/transfer-exam-credit/exam-credit/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Degree Progress Unit website</a><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">.</span></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "f2756f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralTitle",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 6,
      "content": "MUSIC B.A.",
      "contentHtml": null
    },
    {
      "id": "f4756f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralText",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 7,
      "content": "Prospective transfer students are strongly encouraged to contact the Music Undergraduate Programs Coordinator &lt; music@ucsc.edu &gt; to schedule a Zoom or phone advising appointment prior to applying. PREPARATION FOR THE MAJOR Theory The Music Department encourages transfer students to take the Theory Placement Exam and seek academic counseling before transfer the year before they apply, as placement results have the potential to affect time-to-degree for students, depending on major track requirements. Placement results are valid for a calendar year. Although not required for admission, prospective transfer students are encouraged to complete college-level music theory courses prior to transferring. Refer to the \" Recommended Preparation \" section below for courses approved to articulate to the major’s Western music theory requirements. Performance Students are encouraged to begin performing ensembles and/or applied lessons on a specific instrument or voice before transfer. Upon transfer, community college ensemble and lesson participation can be petitioned to count toward the major requirements. Additional Information for Transfer Students are encouraged to complete the California General Education Transfer Curriculum (Cal-GETC) or all UC Santa Cruz general education requirements before transferring. For guidance on incorporating Cal-GETC into your academic plan, consult your community college counselor. Visit the Music Department website to learn more about this major. UC Santa Cruz General Catalog: Music B.A. Program Statement",
      "contentHtml": "<p class=\"highlight\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Prospective transfer students are strongly encouraged to contact the Music Undergraduate Programs Coordinator &lt;</span><a href=\"mailto:music@ucsc.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-size: 14px;\">music@ucsc.edu</a><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&gt;&nbsp;to schedule a Zoom or phone advising appointment prior to applying.</span></p><p><br></p><h2><strong>PREPARATION FOR THE MAJOR</strong></h2><p><strong style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><u>Theory</u></strong></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">The Music Department encourages transfer students to take the </span><a href=\"https://music.ucsc.edu/academics/theory-placement-exam/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>Theory Placement Exam</strong></a><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"> and seek academic counseling before transfer the year before they apply, as placement results have the potential to affect time-to-degree for students, depending on major track requirements. Placement results are valid for a calendar year. </span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Although not required for admission, prospective transfer students are encouraged to complete college-level music theory courses prior to transferring. Refer to the \"</span><strong style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Recommended Preparation</strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">\" section below for courses approved to articulate to the major’s Western music theory requirements.</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><u>Performance</u></strong></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Students are encouraged to begin performing ensembles and/or applied lessons on a specific instrument or voice before transfer. Upon transfer, community college ensemble and lesson participation can be petitioned to count toward the major requirements. </span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><h2><strong>Additional Information for Transfer</strong></h2><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Students are encouraged to complete the </span><a href=\"https://admission.universityofcalifornia.edu/admission-requirements/transfer-requirements/preparing-to-transfer/general-education-igetc/cal-getc/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>California General Education Transfer Curriculum (Cal-GETC)</strong></a><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"> or all UC Santa Cruz general education requirements before transferring. For guidance on incorporating Cal-GETC into your academic plan, consult your community college counselor.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Visit the </span><a href=\"https://music.ucsc.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Music Department website</a><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"> to learn more about this major.</span></p><p><a href=\"https://catalog.ucsc.edu/en/current/general-catalog/academic-units/arts-division/music/music-ba/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-size: 14px;\">UC Santa Cruz General Catalog: Music B.A. Program Statement</a></p>"
